            <fr:title text="Why Functional Analysis?">Why Functional Analysis?</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Why Functional Analysis?</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Extension of Linear Algebra to <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0005.xml" addr="FA-0005" title="Infinite Dimensions">Infinite Dimensions</fr:link></fr:li>
<fr:li>Deals with Functions (<fr:link type="local" href="FA-0006.xml" addr="FA-0006" title="Space of Continuous Functions">Space of Continuous Functions</fr:link>) as the primary objects/unknowns</fr:li>
<fr:li>Merges <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0007">Analysis</fr:link> and <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0008">Linear Algebra</fr:link></fr:li>
<fr:li>Necessity for exploring different <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0009.xml" addr="FA-0009" title="Distance Measure">Distance Measure</fr:link>s in <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0010.xml" addr="FA-0010" title="Pointwise Convergence">infinite dimensions</fr:link></fr:li>
<fr:li>Clarification, Rigorisation, and Unification of concepts</fr:li>
<fr:li>Applications (<fr:link type="local" href="FA-0011.xml" addr="FA-0011" title="Kronecker delta">Differential Equations</fr:link>, Numerical Methods, <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0012.xml" addr="FA-0012" title="Inner product space">Calculus of Variations</fr:link>, Signal Processing, Integral Equations)</fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
